\date{2025-02-03}
\title{Covariant Fibrations in STT}
\author{samtoth}

\p{
    Given a (Rezk or Segal) type #{B}, we define a predicate on families over #{B}:

##{
  \textrm{isCov}(P : B \to \mathcal{U}) : \mathcal{U}_{-1} = \Pi_{(x,y : B)}\Pi_{f : Hom_B(x,y)}\Pi_{p_x : P(x)} \textrm{isContr}(\Sigma_{(p_y : P(y))} Hom_P^f(p_x,p_y)) 
}
}